{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1773058988,"nonce":"+eOh3sRALagMvxjF46VCo7LiQho=","title":"Add Turbo cache cleanup to Stimulus controllers","message":"Several Stimulus controllers manipulate DOM or hold library instances but have no `disconnect()` method and no `turbo:before-cache` handler. They are susceptible to stale state when navigating with the browser back button.\n\n**Controllers affected:**\n\n1. **datepicker_controller** — Pikaday library instance never destroyed\n2. **accessories_input_controller** — Dynamically clones form elements\n3. **links_input_controller** — Dynamically clones form elements\n4. **readmore_controller** — Creates wrapper div around content\n5. **tags_input_controller** — Tagify library instance never destroyed\n6. **timeago_controller** — TimeAgo library instance never destroyed\n7. **unique_items_controller** — Dynamically adds/removes item rows\n8. **inline_tabs_controller** — Bootstrap Modal state\n9. **sidebar_cart_controller** — Has a turbo:load handler but uses document-level listener that leaks\n\n**Fix pattern** (established in #216 / autocomplete controller fix):\n- Add `disconnect()` to clean up event listeners and library instances\n- Add `turbo:before-cache` handler to reset DOM to a clean state before caching\n- Store references to dynamically created elements for proper cleanup\n- Call library-specific teardown methods (e.g. Pikaday `destroy()`, Tagify `destroy()`, autoComplete `unInit()`)","files":null}]}